title: Two nameless bodies washed up on the beach. Here are their stories
description: When two bodies wearing identical wetsuits washed ashore in Norway and the Netherlands, journalist Anders Fjellberg and photographer Tomm Christiansen started a search to answer the question: who were these people? What they found and reported in Norway's "Dagbladet" is that everybody has a name, everybody has a story and everybody is someone.
author: Anders Fjellberg
keywords: TED, talks, Europe, Middle East, death, global issues, identity, journalism, war, Syria
